author: Family of 5 dead after SUV goes into lake
title: Radwanska wins Tianjin tournament
text:
Radwanska wins Tianjin tournament AFP 1 day ago Â© Provided by AFP Agnieszka Radwanska beats Danka Kovinic in the Tianjin Open final to secure her place at the WTA Finals in Singapore next month Poland's Agnieszka Radwanska secured a slot in the WTA Finals with a straight-sets victory in the final of China's Tianjin Open on Sunday.
AdChoices The 6-1, 6-2 win by the world number six over the much lower ranked Montenegrin Danka Kovinic ensures her place at the WTA Finals in Singapore next month.
The second-seeded Pole broke five times without being broken herself to dismiss Kovinic in just 58 minutes.
The $500,000 (440,000-euro) WTA tournament has seen a run of upsets and has been beset by heavy air pollution.
